Reasoning: The paper deals with graph theory and its related problems. Specifically, it introduces and studies the concepts of thinness and proper thinness of a graph, which are important graph parameters. These parameters have applications in various areas of computer science, such as computational geometry, data mining, and network analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which covers topics related to graph theory, combinatorics, and discrete structures. Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), which also deal with graph-related problems and their computational complexity.
